verbose_text: The levels of CRP (57.70 +/-55.81 vs. 40.01 +/-44.70 mg/L, P < 0.001), anti-CCP (924.14 +/-1163.66 vs. 754.97 +/-1073.50 RU/ml, P = 0.012), and RF (657.81 +/-895.06 vs. 352.66 +/-589.22 IU/ml, P = 0.001), as well as ESR (75.99 +/-31.46 vs. 65.32 +/-31.63 mm/h, P = 0.005) were significantly higher in RA patients with ILD compared with those without ILD.
